com.bluegosling.collections.queues

Class PriorityQueues

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bluegosling.collections.queues.PriorityQueues

  • public final class PriorityQueues
extends Object
    Utility methods for working with instances of PriorityQueue (not to be mistaken for PriorityQueue).

    The meat of this class includes a useful base class for value types that are stored into priority queues, and methods for adapting a priority queue to the standard Queue interface.

    • Method Detail

      • asQueue

        public static <E> OrderedQueue<E> asQueue(PriorityQueue<E,E> priorityQueue)
        Returns a view of a PriorityQueue as an OrderedQueue. The elements in the queue have intrinsic priority instead of a separate explicit priority. So when added to the given queue, the priority value is the same as the element value.
        Parameters:
        priorityQueue - a priority queue
        Returns:
        a view of the given priority queue as a OrderedQueue

      • asQueue

        public static <E,Q extends MeldablePriorityQueue<E,E,Q>> PriorityQueues.MeldableQueue<E> asQueue(Q priorityQueue)
        Returns a view of a MeldablePriorityQueue as a MeldableOrderedQueue. The elements in the queue have intrinsic priority instead of a separate explicit priority. So when added to the given queue, the priority value is the same as the element value. Attempting to meld the returned queue with another whose underlying priority queue is not actually meldable will also result in a ClassCastException.
        Parameters:
        priorityQueue - a priority queue
        Returns:
        a view of the given priority queue as a MeldableOrderedQueue
